2022 was a wonderful year for me professionally. I had the opportunity to work with the most talented and creative people. I photographed more beautiful homes than I can count. I thank my stars everyday that I left wedding photography to pursue my true passion and that the universe opened a path for me to be successful at this new endeavor. If I have learned anything from making a career change, it is that doing work I love is so important to my sense of contentment and happiness. Life is too short to be unhappy in our careers. 
Personally, 2022 had some very difficult challenges including the unexpected and tragic death of my sister, my brother’s stroke, continued care for my disabled mother, and to top it all off my dad’s heart attack over the holidays. It makes me start to sweat just typing that all out😑😓
But in between the challenges were so many beautiful moments and experiences. My little sister getting married for the first time at age 38. My children growing and thriving. Our summer vacation to the beaches of California. Hosting parties and opening our home to our beloved friends and family. Getting my entire family on the ski slopes for first time in 17 years, which has always been a life goal for me.
Life is so beautiful, and so hard all at the same time. 
Cheers to 2023 and all that it will bring to us and teach us ❤️❤️❤️
